    <section id="cost-of-waiting">
        <h2>Why Every Day Without Action Counts: The Cost of Waiting</h2>
        <p>Living in Tulsa means your roof works overtime. As experienced roofing contractors Tulsa OK residents rely on, we’ve seen how small issues can become major headaches faster than an Oklahoma storm rolls in. Ignoring those initial warning signs isn’t just risky—it’s like leaving your front door open during tornado season!</p>
        <p>Water damage spreads like a superhero’s arch-nemesis, silently wreaking havoc on your home’s structure, creating toxic mold, and threatening your family’s safety. The longer you wait, the more your wallet feels the pain. A simple, preemptive repair today could save you thousands tomorrow.</p>

        <h3>The Hidden Dangers of Procrastination:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Dangerous Mold and Mildew:</strong> Water infiltration creates the perfect breeding ground for mold inside your walls and attic, posing serious health risks.</li>
            <li><strong>Skyrocketing Energy Bills:</strong> Damaged, wet, or compressed insulation loses its R-value, forcing your HVAC system to work harder and driving up your monthly costs.</li>
            <li><strong>Structural Compromise:</strong> Ongoing leaks can rot the wooden decking, rafters, and trusses that compromise your home’s core integrity.</li>
            <li><strong>Decreased Property Value:</strong> A major roof issue found during an inspection can derail a home sale, leading to significant negotiation losses.</li>
            <li><strong>Unwanted Pests:</strong> Holes, gaps, and soft spots in your roof are invitations for squirrels, rats, and insects to find a new home in your attic.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>We’ve seen too many Tulsa families learn these lessons the hard way. That’s why we’re on a mission to help homeowners spot problems early and fix them fast.</p>
